The [scm-tags-plugin|https://stash.atlassian.com/projects/STASH/repos/stash-scm-tags-plugin/browse] is programmed to delete its cache entries when it [shutdowns|https://stash.atlassian.com/projects/STASH/repos/stash-scm-tags-plugin/browse/src/main/scala/com/atlassian/stash/internal/tag/DefaultScmTagService.scala#74]. However, stale entries has been observed in the Stash team's internal instance:

{quote}
Bryan: stash-dev has ~30k cache files, and most of them are in scm-tags
{noformat}
node481:/opt/j2ee/domains/atlassian.com/stash-cluster/install/home/caches/scm-tags$ ls -lrt | head
total 75176
-rw-r--r-- 1 atlstash user     0 Nov 18 13:37 cache-entry5832135393360417073
-rw-r--r-- 1 atlstash user     0 Nov 18 13:37 cache-entry4191256713607527145
-rw-r--r-- 1 atlstash user     0 Nov 18 13:37 cache-entry9114455448116455716
-rw-r--r-- 1 atlstash user     0 Nov 18 13:37 cache-entry4878348930357163328
-rw-r--r-- 1 atlstash user   406 Nov 18 13:37 cache-entry4602207029660125443
{noformat}
{quote}

This is pretty minor, as there are no built in Pull Request settings that can actually fail to validate, but it may cause problems for plugins.

If there is an error on the PR settings page, the build status will be reset to "enabled" and "1" because of the logic in {{com.atlassian.stash.internal.build.hook.RequiredBuildsFormFragment#doError}}: 

{code}
    @Override
    public void doError(Appendable appendable, Map<String, String[]> requestParams, Map<String, Collection<String>> fieldErrors, Map<String, Object> context) throws IOException {
        context.put(FIELD_KEY, 1); // default to 1 since the submitted number of required builds was either negative, too large or not a number
        context.put(FIELD_MAX_VALUE, MAX_BUILDS);
        context.put(FIELD_ERRORS, fieldErrors);
        renderView(appendable, context);
    }
{code}

{{doError}} is actually called if _any_ setting fails to validate, not just this particular form fragment (see the contract on {{com.atlassian.stash.ui.ContextualFormFragment#doError}}). 

{{com.atlassian.stash.internal.plugin.hooks.approvers.RequiredApproversFormFragment#doError}} suffers from the same problem.

The correct behaviour should retrieve the actual value from the form submission in the request parameters. The {{AutoUnapproveFormFragment}} in the {{stash-auto-unapprove-plugin}} does it correctly. See https://bitbucket.org/atlassian/stash-auto-unapprove-plugin/src/dc27236927c67e04be28d6a989bf30c895ed9c71/src/main/java/com/atlassian/stash/unapprove/AutoUnapproveFormFragment.java?at=master#cl-36

There's a CSS styling when Stash renders Markdown:
.markup h1, .markup h2
{ margin: 10px 0 20px 0; }

The header is closer to the previous content than the following content. Any of the following look much nicer:

.markup h1, .markup h2
{ margin: 10px 0; }
.markup h1, .markup h2
{ margin: 20px 0; }
.markup h1, .markup h2
{ margin: 10px 0 20px; }

When trying to use {{BranchInformationService}} in a Stash plugin, adding {{<component-import key="branchInformationService" interface="com.atlassian.stash.branch.info.BranchInformationService"/>}} to {{atlassian-plugin.xml}} results in the following error:

{code}2014-12-02 22:11:22,208 ERROR [localhost-startStop-1] c.a.plugin.osgi.factory.OsgiPlugin Never resolved service '&branchInformationService' for plugin 'com.jeffthms.stash.myplugin' with filter (objectClass=com.atlassian.stash.branch.info.BranchInformationService){code}

This is because {{BranchInformationService}} is not published for other plugins to use. Since it's [publicly listed|https://developer.atlassian.com/static/javadoc/stash/3.5.0/branch-utils/reference/com/atlassian/stas] it should be available to be imported.

h4. Problem Statement
When transitioning a JIRA issue with a blank value in a _date picker_ custom field, Stash POST a empty String value to Jira when transitioning an issue from Stash. The request will be rejected by JIRA with error message: {{Error parsing date string}}

h4. Example
Example request payload by Stash, {{customfield_10000}} being the date picker field custom field:
{code}{"fields":{"assignee":{"name":"admin"},"customfield_10002":"","resolution":{"name":"Fixed"},"customfield_10000":""},"transition":{"id":"2"}}{code}
Example response:
{code}{"errors":[{"context":"customfield_10000","message":"Error parsing date string: ","exceptionName":null}]}{code}

h4. Suggestion
Stash should send a NULL value rather than a blank String to JIRA when date is not specified. Example:
{code}{"fields":{"assignee":{"name":"admin"},"customfield_10002":"","resolution":{"name":"Fixed"},"customfield_10000":null},"transition":{"id":"2"}}{code}

It will be good if the path query parameter is set as optional for the following Stash API:

{noformat}
/rest/api/1.0/projects/<projectKey>/repos/<repositorySlug>/commits/<commitId>/comments
{noformat}

The {{[/rest/branch-utils/1.0/projects/\{projectKey\}/repos/\{repositorySlug\}/branches/info/\{changesetId\}|https://developer.atlassian.com/static/rest/stash/3.4.3/stash-branch-utils-rest.html#idp64912]}} REST endpoint documentation states the following:

{quote}Gets the branch information associated with a single changeset from a given repository.{quote}

The documentation should be updated to include clarification that once a commit is on {{master}} (or whatever the default branch is) Stash considers it "merged" and will only show this commit as existing on {{master}}. Without this clarification, it's easy to think that all branches that this commit exists on should be returned regardless if it exists on {{master}}.

When creating the pull request, I see in the preview diff

{code}
git diff $(git merge-base my-branch target-branch) my-branch
{code}

This does not represent the changes that will be made.

Better:

{code}
git diff target-branch my-branch
{code}

Best:

What I will see in the "Diff" tab of the pull request...i.e. the diff of the merge. This way, I can see merge conflicts too.
